  "title": "Admin Executive Temp",
  "description": "<p>Contract: 12 months<br /><br /><strong>Job Scope:</strong> </p><p>To provide administrative and operational support in managing public and stakeholder communications, data collection and reporting, site visits, and general administration related to school canteen and school bus matters.</p><p>Key responsibilities:<br /><br />Public Correspondence </p><ul><li>Draft clear, accurate and timely replies to enquiries and feedback from members of the public</li><li>Ensure responses are aligned with established policies and guidelines</li></ul><p>Stakeholder management</p><ul><li>Manage and respond to queries from stakeholders e.g. schools relating to school canteen operations and school bus services</li></ul><p>Site Visits and Issue Resolution</p><ul><li>Conduct site visits to schools to assess canteen operations and school bus services </li><li>Report on operational issues and work with relevant parties to troubleshoot problems </li><li>Document findings and recommendations from site visit</li></ul><p>Surveys and Feedback Collection</p><ul><li>Assist in the planning, administration, and conduct of surveys</li><li>Compile survey responses and ensure proper documentation of findings</li></ul><p>Data management and Reporting</p><ul><li>Perform data entry accurately and maintain databases and records </li><li>Analyse data and prepare summaries, reports and presentation materials for management’s review</li></ul><p>Records Management</p><ul><li>Maintain proper filing of documents in accordance with record-keeping requirements</li><li>Ensure information is organised, updated and easily retrievable</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Location</strong>: Grange Road<br /><br /><strong>Working Hours</strong>: Office Hours<br /><br /><strong>Salary</strong>: <br />$2580 (now till 30 Jun 26)<br />$2760 (1 Jul 26 onwards)<br /><br /><br />EA License No.: 96C4864</p><p>Reg No.: R25128798 HUANG QIMENG</p>",
